#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:23
msgid ""
"Here the NMHSs input the different types of hazards they monitor. They can "
"select the hazards from a WMO predefined list of hazards or create a new "
"custom hazard/event type. Each hazard type can be associated with an Icon"
msgstr ""
"Hapa NMHS huingiza aina tofauti za hatari wanazofuatilia. Wanaweza kuchagua "
"hatari kutoka kwa orodha iliyofafanuliwa awali ya WMO ya hatari au kuunda "
"hatari maalum/aina ya tukio. Kila aina ya hatari inaweza kuhusishwa na Ikoni"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:26
msgid ""
"![CAP Hazard Types](../../_static/images/cap/CAP_hazard_types.png \"CAP "
"Hazard Types\")"
msgstr ""
"![Aina za Hatari za CAP](../../_static/images/cap/CAP_hazard_types.png "
"\"Aina za Hatari za CAP\")"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:26
msgid "CAP Hazard Types"
msgstr "Aina za Hatari za CAP"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:28
msgid "Assigning Event Codes"
msgstr "Kukabidhi Misimbo ya Tukio"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:30
msgid "Each Hazard type should be associated with the following:"
msgstr "Kila aina ya Hatari inapaswa kuhusishwa na yafuatayo:"

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:32
msgid ""
"**Hazard Type**: The name of the hazard type. You can select from the WMO "
"predefined list or create a new one."
msgstr ""
"**Aina ya Hatari**: Jina la aina ya hatari. Unaweza kuchagua kutoka kwa "
"orodha iliyofafanuliwa awali ya WMO au kuunda mpya."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:33
msgid ""
"**Category**: The category of the hazard type, as defined in the CAP "
"Protocol."
msgstr ""
"**Aina**: Aina ya aina ya hatari, kama inavyofafanuliwa katika Itifaki ya "
"CAP."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:34
msgid ""
"**Event Code**: The event code of the hazard type, as defined in [OASIS "
"Event Term List for use with CAP](https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/cap-"
"etl/v1.2/cn01/cap-etl-v1.2-cn01.html). When selecting the event code, ensure"
" you have the correct hazard Category selected, as the event codes are "
"filtered by the selected hazard Category. You can confirm the event code by "
"checking the [OASIS Event Terms](https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/cap-"
"etl/v1.2/cn01/cap-etl-v1.2-cn01.html). Scroll down to the Appendix B "
"section, where the event codes are listed with the corresponding Category."
msgstr ""
"**Msimbo wa Tukio**: Msimbo wa tukio wa aina ya hatari, kama "
"inavyofafanuliwa katika [Orodha ya Masharti ya Tukio ya OASIS kwa matumizi "
"na CAP](https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/cap-etl/v1.2/cn01/cap-"
"etl-v1.2-cn01.html). Wakati wa kuchagua msimbo wa tukio, hakikisha kuwa "
"umechagua Kitengo sahihi cha hatari, kwani misimbo ya tukio huchujwa na "
"Kitengo cha hatari kilichochaguliwa. Unaweza kuthibitisha msimbo wa tukio "
"kwa kuangalia [Masharti ya Tukio la OASIS](https://docs.oasis-"
"open.org/emergency/cap-etl/v1.2/cn01/cap-etl-v1.2-cn01.html). Tembeza chini "
"hadi sehemu ya Kiambatisho B, ambapo misimbo ya tukio imeorodheshwa na "
"Kategoria inayolingana."

#: ../../_docs/manage_cap/CAP-Base-Settings.md:41
msgid ""
"![CAP Event Codes](../../_static/images/cap/cap_event_codes.png \"CAP Event "
"Codes\")"
msgstr ""
"![Misimbo ya Tukio ya CAP](../../_static/images/cap/cap_event_codes.png "
"\"Misimbo ya Tukio ya CAP\")"

