"[https://docs.docker.com/desktop](https://docs.docker.com/desktop) na "
"[https://docs.docker.com/compose/install](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install)"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:58
msgid ""
"Docker version 19.03 is the minimum required to build Climweb. It is "
"strongly advised however that you install the latest version of Docker "
"available. Please check that your docker is up to date by running `docker "
"-v`."
msgstr ""
"Toleo la Docker 19.03 ndio kiwango cha chini kinachohitajika kuunda Climweb."
" Inashauriwa sana hata hivyo kwamba usakinishe toleo la hivi karibuni la "
"Docker linalopatikana. Tafadhali hakikisha kuwa docker yako imesasishwa kwa "
"kuendesha `docker -v`."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:62
msgid ""
"You will also need git installed which you can do by following the "
"instructions on [https://www.linode.com/docs/development/version-"
"control/how-to-install-git-on-linux-mac-and-"
"windows](https://www.linode.com/docs/development/version-control/how-to-"
"install-git-on-linux-mac-and-windows)."
msgstr ""
"Utahitaji pia git kusakinishwa ambayo unaweza kufanya kwa kufuata maagizo "
"kwenye [https://www.linode.com/docs/development/version-control/how-to-"
"install-git-on-linux-mac-and-windows]( "
"https://www.linode.com/docs/development/version-control/how-to-install-"
"uxgit-windows-).-"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:65
msgid ""
"Once you have finished installing all the required software you should be "
"able to run the following commands in your terminal."
msgstr ""
"Mara baada ya kumaliza kusakinisha programu zote zinazohitajika unapaswa "
"kuwa na uwezo wa kuendesha amri zifuatazo katika terminal yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:78
msgid ""
"If all commands return something similar as described in the example, then "
"you are ready to proceed!"
msgstr ""
"Ikiwa amri zote zitarudisha kitu sawa kama ilivyoelezewa katika mfano, basi "
"uko tayari kuendelea!"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:80
msgid "Starting the development environment"
msgstr "Kuanzisha mazingira ya maendeleo"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:82
msgid ""
"First, you need to clone the repository. Execute the following commands to "
"clone the main branch. If you are not familiar with git clone, this will "
"download a copy of Climweb’s code to your computer."
msgstr ""
"Kwanza, unahitaji kuiga hazina. Tekeleza amri zifuatazo ili kuiga tawi kuu. "
"Ikiwa haujui git clone, hii itapakua nakala ya nambari ya Climweb kwenye "
"kompyuta yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:92
msgid ""
"Now that we have our copy of the repo and have changed directories to the "
"newly created climweb, we can bring up the containers."
msgstr ""
"Sasa kwa kuwa tunayo nakala yetu ya repo na tumebadilisha saraka hadi "
"climweb mpya iliyoundwa, tunaweza kuleta vyombo."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:95
msgid ""
"If you do not want to use the provided `dev.sh` script, you can run the "
"following command to start the development environment:"
msgstr ""
"Ikiwa hutaki kutumia hati ya `dev.sh` iliyotolewa, unaweza kutekeleza amri "
"ifuatayo ili kuanza mazingira ya uendelezaji:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:103
msgid ""
"Note that the `docker-compose.dev.yml` file is used to override the default "
"`docker-compose.yml` file with development specific settings."
msgstr ""
"Kumbuka kuwa faili ya `docker-compose.dev.yml` inatumika kubatilisha faili "
"chaguo-msingi `docker-compose.yml` kwa mipangilio mahususi ya usanidi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:107
msgid "Accessing the web application"
msgstr "Kufikia programu ya wavuti"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:109
msgid ""
"Once the containers are up and running, you can access the Climweb "
"application in your web browser at "
"[http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000). The port can be changed in "
"the `.env` file if needed by modifying the `CLIMWEB_DEV_PORT` variable."
msgstr ""
"Mara tu vyombo vinapoanza kutumika, unaweza kufikia programu ya Climweb "
"katika kivinjari chako cha wavuti katika "
"[http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000). Lango linaweza kubadilishwa "
"katika faili ya `.env` ikihitajika kwa kurekebisha kigezo cha "
"`CLIMWEB_DEV_PORT`."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:114
msgid "Creating a superuser"
msgstr "Kuunda mtumiaji mkuu"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:116
msgid ""
"To create a superuser for the Climweb application, you can run the following"
" command in a separate terminal window:"
msgstr ""
"Ili kuunda mtumiaji mkuu kwa programu ya Climweb, unaweza kuendesha amri "
"ifuatayo kwenye dirisha tofauti la terminal:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:122
msgid "Keep the container running"
msgstr "Weka chombo kukimbia"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/running-dev-environment.md:124
msgid ""
"The containers need to keep running while you are developing. They also "
"monitor file changes and update automatically, so you don’t need to worry "
"about reloading. Any change to the code will trigger a reload and you can "
"see the changes immediately."
msgstr ""
"Vyombo vinahitaji kuendelea kukimbia wakati unatengeneza. Pia hufuatilia "
"mabadiliko ya faili na kusasisha kiotomatiki, kwa hivyo huna haja ya kuwa na"
" wasiwasi kuhusu kupakia upya. Mabadiliko yoyote kwenye msimbo yataanzisha "
"upakiaji upya na unaweza kuona mabadiliko mara moja."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:1
msgid "Creating a Plugin"
msgstr "Kuunda Programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:3
msgid ""
"In this guide we will dive into how to create a Climweb plugin, discuss the "
"plugin architecture and give an example plugin to get inspiration from and "
"discuss how to publish your plugin."
msgstr ""
"Katika mwongozo huu tutazama katika jinsi ya kuunda programu-jalizi ya "
"Climweb, kujadili usanifu wa programu-jalizi na kutoa mfano wa programu-"
"jalizi ili kupata msukumo kutoka na kujadili jinsi ya kuchapisha programu-"
"jalizi yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:6
msgid "Plugin Architecture"
msgstr "Usanifu wa programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:8
msgid ""
"A ClimWeb Plugin is fundamentally a folder named after the plugin. The "
"folder should be a [Django/Wagtail "
"App](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/5.1/ref/applications/)"
msgstr ""
"Programu-jalizi ya ClimWeb kimsingi ni folda iliyopewa jina la programu-"
"jalizi. Folda inapaswa kuwa [Programu ya "
"Django/Wagtail](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/5.1/ref/applications/)"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:11
msgid "Initialize your plugin from the plugin template"
msgstr "Anzisha programu-jalizi yako kutoka kwa kiolezo cha programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:13
msgid ""
"The plugin template is a "
"[cookiecutter](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html)"
" template that generates a plugin with the required structure and files. "
"This ensures that the plugin follows the expected structure and can be "
"easily installed into climweb."
msgstr ""
"Kiolezo cha programu-jalizi ni kiolezo cha "
"[cookiecutter](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html)"
" ambacho hutengeneza programu-jalizi yenye muundo na faili zinazohitajika. "
"Hii inahakikisha kuwa programu-jalizi inafuata muundo unaotarajiwa na "
"inaweza kusakinishwa kwa urahisi kwenye climweb."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:17
msgid ""
"To instantiate the template, execute the following commands from the "
"directory where you want to create the plugin:"
msgstr ""
"Ili kusisitiza kiolezo, tekeleza amri zifuatazo kutoka kwenye saraka ambapo "
"unataka kuunda programu-jalizi:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:24
msgid ""
"For more details on using the plugin boilerplate, you can follow the [step-"
"by-step guide](#plugin-boilerplate) on creating a plugin using the plugin "
"boilerplate."
msgstr ""
"Kwa maelezo zaidi kuhusu kutumia bamba la programu-jalizi, unaweza kufuata "
"[mwongozo wa hatua kwa hatua](#plugin-boilerplate) kuhusu kuunda programu-"
"jalizi kwa kutumia bamba la programu-jalizi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:27
msgid "Plugin Installation API"
msgstr "API ya Usakinishaji wa programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:29
msgid ""
"A Climweb docker image contains the following bash scripts that are used to "
"install plugins. They can be used to install a plugin into an existing adl "
"container at runtime. `install_plugin.sh` can be used to install a plugin "
"from an url, a git repo or a local folder on the filesystem."
msgstr ""
"Picha ya Climweb docker ina hati zifuatazo za bash ambazo hutumika "
"kusakinisha programu-jalizi. Zinaweza kutumika kusakinisha programu-jalizi "
"kwenye kontena iliyopo ya adl wakati wa utekelezaji. `install_plugin.sh` "
"inaweza kutumika kusakinisha programu-jalizi kutoka kwa url, git repo au "
"folda ya ndani kwenye mfumo wa faili."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:33
msgid ""
"You can find these scripts in the following locations in the built images:"
msgstr ""
"Unaweza kupata hati hizi katika maeneo yafuatayo katika picha zilizojengwa:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:35
msgid "`/deploy/plugins/install_plugin.sh`"
msgstr "`/deploy/plugins/install_plugin.sh`"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:37
msgid "On this repo, you can find the scripts in the `deploy/plugins` folder."
msgstr ""
"Kwenye repo hili, unaweza kupata maandishi kwenye folda ya `deploy/plugins`."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:39
msgid ""
"These scripts expect a ClimWeb plugin to follow the conventions described "
"below:"
msgstr ""
"Maandishi haya yanatarajia programu-jalizi ya ClimWeb kufuata mikusanyiko "
"iliyoelezewa hapa chini:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:41
msgid "Plugin File Structure"
msgstr "Muundo wa Faili ya Programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:43
msgid ""
"The `install_plugin.sh` script expect your plugin to have a specific "
"structure as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Hati ya `install_plugin.sh` inatarajia programu-jalizi yako kuwa na muundo "
"maalum kama ifuatavyo:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:55
msgid ""
"The folder contains three bash files which will be automatically called by "
"climweb's plugin scripts during installation and uninstallation of the "
"plugin. You can use these scripts to perform extra build steps, installation"
" of packages and other docker container build steps required by your plugin."
msgstr ""
"Folda ina faili tatu za bash ambazo zitaitwa kiotomatiki na hati-jalizi za "
"climweb wakati wa usakinishaji na uondoaji wa programu-jalizi. Unaweza "
"kutumia hati hizi kutekeleza hatua za ziada za ujenzi, usakinishaji wa "
"vifurushi na hatua zingine za uundaji wa kontena zinazohitajika na programu-"
"jalizi yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:59
msgid ""
"`build.sh`: Called on container startup if a runtime installation is "
"occurring."
msgstr ""
"`build.sh`: Wito wa kuanzisha kontena ikiwa usakinishaji wa wakati wa "
"utekelezaji unafanyika."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:60
msgid ""
"`runtime_setup.sh`: Called the first time a container starts up after the "
"plugin has been installed, useful for running superuser commands on the "
"container."
msgstr ""
"`runtime_setup.sh`: Inaitwa mara ya kwanza ambapo kontena inapowashwa baada "
"ya programu-jalizi kusakinishwa, ni muhimu kwa kutekeleza amri za mtumiaji "
"mkuu kwenye kontena."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:62
msgid ""
"`uninstall.sh`: Called on uninstall, the database will be available and so "
"any backwards migrations should be run here."
msgstr ""
"`uninstall.sh`: Wito wa kusakinisha, hifadhidata itapatikana na kwa hivyo "
"uhamishaji wowote wa kurudi nyuma unapaswa kuendeshwa hapa."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:65
msgid "The plugin info file"
msgstr "Faili ya maelezo ya programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:67
msgid ""
"The `climweb_plugin_info.json` file is a json file, in your root plugin "
"folder, containing metadata about your plugin. It should have the following "
"JSON structure:"
msgstr ""
"Faili ya `climweb_plugin_info.json` ni faili ya json, katika folda yako ya "
"programu-jalizi ya msingi, iliyo na metadata kuhusu programu-jalizi yako. "
"Inapaswa kuwa na muundo ufuatao wa JSON:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:83
msgid "Expected plugin structure when installing from a git repository"
msgstr ""
"Muundo wa programu-jalizi unaotarajiwa wakati wa kusakinisha kutoka kwa "
"hazina ya git"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:85
msgid ""
"When installing a plugin from git, the repo should contain a single plugins "
"folder, inside which there should a single plugin folder following the "
"structure above and has the same name as your plugin."
msgstr ""
"Wakati wa kusakinisha programu-jalizi kutoka kwa git, repo inapaswa kuwa na "
"folda ya programu-jalizi moja, ambayo ndani yake kunapaswa kuwa na folda "
"moja ya programu-jalizi inayofuata muundo hapo juu na ina jina sawa na "
"programu-jalizi yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:88
msgid ""
"By default, the `plugin boilerplate` generates a repository with this "
"structure."
msgstr ""
"Kwa chaguo-msingi, `plate ya programu-jalizi` hutengeneza hazina iliyo na "
"muundo huu."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:90
msgid "For example a conforming git repo should contain something like:"
msgstr "Kwa mfano git repo inayolingana inapaswa kuwa na kitu kama:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:104
#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-boilerplate.md:1
msgid "Plugin Boilerplate"
msgstr "Plugin Boilerplate"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:106
msgid ""
"With the plugin boilerplate you can easily create a new plugin and setup a "
"docker development environment that installs adl as a dependency. This can "
"easily be installed via cookiecutter."
msgstr ""
"Ukiwa na bati ya programu-jalizi unaweza kuunda programu-jalizi mpya kwa "
"urahisi na kusanidi mazingira ya ukuzaji wa kizimbani ambayo husakinisha adl"
" kama tegemezi. Hii inaweza kusakinishwa kwa urahisi kupitia cookiecutter."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:109
msgid "Creating a plugin"
msgstr "Inaunda programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:111
msgid ""
"To use the plugin boilerplate you must first install the "
"[Cookiecutter](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html)"
" tool (`pip install cookiecutter`)."
msgstr ""
"Ili kutumia boilerplate ya programu-jalizi lazima kwanza usakinishe zana ya "
"[Cookiecutter](https://cookiecutter.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html)"
" (`pip install cookiecutter`)."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:114
msgid ""
"Once you have installed Cookiecutter you can execute the following command "
"to create a new ADL plugin from our template. In this guide we will name our"
" plugin “My Climweb Plugin”, however you can choose your own plugin name "
"when prompted to by Cookiecutter."
msgstr ""
"Mara tu unaposakinisha Cookiecutter unaweza kutekeleza amri ifuatayo ili "
"kuunda programu-jalizi mpya ya ADL kutoka kwa kiolezo chetu. Katika mwongozo"
" huu tutaita programu-jalizi yetu \"Plugin Yangu ya Climweb\", hata hivyo "
"unaweza kuchagua jina lako la programu-jalizi unapoombwa na Cookiecutter."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:119
msgid ""
"The python module depends on your chosen plugin name. If we for example go "
"with “My Climweb Plugin” the Django app  name should be my_climweb_plugin"
msgstr ""
"Moduli ya python inategemea jina lako la programu-jalizi ulilochagua. Ikiwa "
"kwa mfano tutaenda na \"My Climweb Plugin\" jina la programu ya Django "
"linapaswa kuwa my_climweb_plugin"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:130
msgid ""
"If you do not see any errors it means that your plugin has been created."
msgstr ""
"Ikiwa huoni makosa yoyote inamaanisha kuwa programu-jalizi yako imeundwa."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:132
msgid "Writing a Plugin"
msgstr "Kuandika Programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:134
msgid ""
"Now you have created a plugin, lets go into more detail of how to actually "
"extend and customize Climweb using your plugin."
msgstr ""
"Sasa umeunda programu-jalizi, hebu tuende kwa undani zaidi jinsi ya kupanua "
"na kubinafsisha Climweb kwa kutumia programu-jalizi yako."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:137
msgid "Storing State"
msgstr "Jimbo la Uhifadhi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:139
msgid "If your plugin needs to store state, you should only ever do this in:"
msgstr ""
"Ikiwa programu-jalizi yako inahitaji kuhifadhi hali, unapaswa kufanya hivi "
"katika:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:141
msgid "The database being used by Climweb"
msgstr "Hifadhidata inayotumiwa na Climweb"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:142
msgid "Using Django’s default storage mechanism"
msgstr "Kwa kutumia utaratibu chaguo-msingi wa kuhifadhi wa Django"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:143
msgid ""
"The Redis being used by Climweb, but only for non-persistent state like a "
"cache that is fine to be destroyed at any moment."
msgstr ""
"Redis inatumiwa na Climweb, lakini kwa hali isiyoendelea kama kache ambayo "
"ni sawa kuharibiwa wakati wowote."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:147
msgid ""
"Never store any state in your plugin folder itself inside the container. "
"This folder is deleted and recreated as part of the plugin installation "
"process and any state you store inside it can be lost."
msgstr ""
"Kamwe usihifadhi hali yoyote kwenye folda yako ya programu-jalizi yenyewe "
"ndani ya kontena. Folda hii inafutwa na kuundwa upya kama sehemu ya mchakato"
" wa usakinishaji wa programu-jalizi na hali yoyote unayohifadhi ndani yake "
"inaweza kupotea."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:151
msgid "Adding Python Requirements"
msgstr "Kuongeza Mahitaji ya Python"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:153
msgid ""
"Your plugin is just a normal python module which will be installed into the "
"Climweb virtual environment using `pip` by `install_plugin.sh`. If using the"
" plugin boilerplate you can add any python requirements to the pip "
"requirements file found at `requirements/base.txt`."
msgstr ""
"Programu-jalizi yako ni moduli ya kawaida ya chatu ambayo itasakinishwa "
"katika mazingira pepe ya Climweb kwa kutumia `pip` na `install_plugin.sh`. "
"Ikiwa unatumia boilerplate ya programu-jalizi unaweza kuongeza mahitaji "
"yoyote ya chatu kwenye faili ya mahitaji ya bomba inayopatikana katika "
"`requirements/base.txt`."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:157
msgid "As a Django/Wagtail App"
msgstr "Kama Programu ya Django/Wagtail"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:159
msgid ""
"When the Climweb Django service starts up it looks for any plugins in the "
"plugin directory. If it finds any it assumes the `src/plugin_name/` sub "
"folder contains a Django App and adds it to the`INSTALLED_APPS`. This means "
"that your plugin must be a Django/Wagtail app whose name exactly matches the"
" name of the plugin folder."
msgstr ""
"Wakati huduma ya Climweb Django inapoanza hutafuta programu-jalizi zozote "
"kwenye saraka ya programu-jalizi. Ikipata yoyote itachukua "
"`src/plugin_name/` folda ndogo ina Programu ya Django na kuiongeza "
"kwenye`INSTALLED_APPS`. Hii inamaanisha kuwa programu-jalizi yako lazima iwe"
" programu ya Django/Wagtail ambayo jina lake linalingana kabisa na jina la "
"folda ya programu-jalizi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:163
msgid ""
"In your plugin’s Django/Wagtail app you can do anything that you normally "
"can do with a Django/Wagtail app such as having migrations, using the "
"`ready()` method to do startup configuration etc."
msgstr ""
"Katika programu-jalizi yako ya Django/Wagtail unaweza kufanya chochote "
"ambacho kwa kawaida unaweza kufanya na programu ya Django/Wagtail kama vile "
"kuwa na uhamaji, kwa kutumia mbinu ya `tayari()` kufanya usanidi wa "
"kuanzisha n.k."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:166
msgid "Publishing your Plugin"
msgstr "Kuchapisha programu-jalizi yako"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/creating-a-plugin.md:168
msgid ""
"The easiest way to share you plugin with others is by making a `public` git "
"repository using GitHub,GitLab or some other git host. Once you have pushed "
"your plugin folder to the git repository then anyone can then install your "
"plugin following the steps in the Plugin Installation guide."
msgstr ""
"Njia rahisi zaidi ya kushiriki programu-jalizi yako na wengine ni "
"kutengeneza hazina ya git ya `umma` kwa kutumia GitHub, GitLab au mwenyeji "
"mwingine wa git. Mara tu unaposukuma folda yako ya programu-jalizi kwenye "
"hazina ya git basi mtu yeyote anaweza kusakinisha programu-jalizi yako kwa "
"kufuata hatua katika mwongozo wa Ufungaji wa programu-jalizi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/index.md:1
#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:28
msgid "Extending Climweb"
msgstr "Kupanua Climweb"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/index.md:3
msgid ""
"At the base, Climweb provides a generic, well researched and tested content "
"structure that addresses most of the needs of the NMHSs, in providing a "
"functional and user-friendly website. This structure is designed to be "
"flexible and extensible, allowing for easy addition of services and products"
" provided by the NMHSs."
msgstr ""
"Kwa msingi, Climweb hutoa muundo wa maudhui wa jumla, uliofanyiwa utafiti "
"vizuri na kujaribiwa ambao unashughulikia mahitaji mengi ya NMHSs, katika "
"kutoa tovuti inayofanya kazi na inayofaa mtumiaji. Muundo huu umeundwa ili "
"uwe rahisi kunyumbulika na kupanuliwa, kuruhusu uongezaji rahisi wa huduma "
"na bidhaa zinazotolewa na NMHSs."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/index.md:7
msgid ""
"However, the needs of each NMHSs may vary, and some may require additional "
"features or customizations to meet their specific requirements. To address "
"this, ClimWeb can be extended by creating new modules, that we call "
"`Plugins`, which can then be integrated into the system."
msgstr ""
"Hata hivyo, mahitaji ya kila NMHS yanaweza kutofautiana, na baadhi yanaweza "
"kuhitaji vipengele vya ziada au ubinafsishaji ili kukidhi mahitaji yao "
"mahususi. Ili kushughulikia hili, ClimWeb inaweza kupanuliwa kwa kuunda "
"moduli mpya, ambazo tunaziita `Plugins`, ambazo zinaweza kuunganishwa kwenye"
" mfumo."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/index.md:11
msgid ""
"These plugins can be used to add new features, modify existing "
"functionality, or integrate with external systems. These can be developed by"
" third-party developers, allowing for a wide range of customization options."
msgstr ""
"Programu-jalizi hizi zinaweza kutumika kuongeza vipengele vipya, kurekebisha"
" utendaji uliopo, au kuunganisha na mifumo ya nje. Hizi zinaweza kuendelezwa"
" na watengenezaji wengine, kuruhusu chaguzi mbalimbali za ubinafsishaji."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-boilerplate.md:3
msgid ""
"With the plugin boilerplate you can easily create a new plugin and setup a "
"docker development environment that installs Climweb as a dependency. This "
"can easily be installed via cookiecutter."
msgstr ""
"Ukiwa na bati ya programu-jalizi unaweza kuunda programu-jalizi mpya kwa "
"urahisi na kusanidi mazingira ya ukuzaji wa kituo ambacho husakinisha "
"Climweb kama tegemezi. Hii inaweza kusakinishwa kwa urahisi kupitia "
"cookiecutter."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:1
msgid "Plugin Installation"
msgstr "Ufungaji wa programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:3
msgid "There are a few ways to install a plugin:"
msgstr "Kuna njia chache za kusakinisha programu-jalizi:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:5
msgid "Using and environment variable"
msgstr "Matumizi na mabadiliko ya mazingira"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:7
msgid ""
"This method assumes you already have the Climweb docker compose services "
"running."
msgstr ""
"Njia hii inadhania kuwa tayari unayo huduma za kutunga za Climweb "
"zinazoendesha."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:9
msgid ""
"You can use the `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS` env variables when using the "
"Climweb docker images to install plugins on startup."
msgstr ""
"Unaweza kutumia vigeu vya env vya `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS` unapotumia "
"picha za kituo cha Climweb kusakinisha programu-jalizi unapowasha."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:12
msgid ""
"The `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS` should be a comma separated list of `https "
"git repo` urls which will be used to download and install plugins on "
"startup."
msgstr ""
"`CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS` inapaswa kuwa orodha iliyotenganishwa kwa koma ya"
" url za `https git repo` ambazo zitatumika kupakua na kusakinisha programu-"
"jalizi inapowashwa."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:15
msgid ""
"After setting the environment variable, you can start the docker container "
"using the following command:"
msgstr ""
"Baada ya kuweka utofauti wa mazingira, unaweza kuanza chombo cha docker kwa "
"kutumia amri ifuatayo:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:21
msgid ""
"These variables will only trigger and installation when found on startup of "
"the container. To uninstall a plugin you must still manually follow the "
"instructions below."
msgstr ""
"Vigezo hivi vitaanzisha na usakinishaji tu wakati vitapatikana wakati wa "
"kuanza kwa kontena. Ili kusanidua programu-jalizi lazima ufuate mwenyewe "
"maagizo hapa chini."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:24
msgid "Caveats when installing into an existing container"
msgstr "Tahadhari wakati wa kusakinisha kwenye chombo kilichopo"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:26
msgid ""
"If you ever delete the container you’ve installed plugins into at runtime "
"and re-create it, the new container is created from the base climweb docker "
"image which does not have any plugins installed."
msgstr ""
"Ukiwahi kufuta kontena ambalo umesakinisha programu-jalizi ndani yake wakati"
" wa utekelezaji na uunda upya, kontena jipya litaundwa kutoka kwa picha ya "
"msingi ya climweb ambayo haijasakinishwa programu jalizi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:29
msgid ""
"However, when a plugin is installed at runtime or build time it is stored in"
" the `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_DIR`which by default is `/climweb/plugins` container "
"folder which should be mounted inside a docker volume. On startup if a "
"plugin is found in this directory which has not yet been installed into the "
"current container it will be re-installed."
msgstr ""
"Hata hivyo, programu-jalizi inaposakinishwa wakati wa utekelezaji au wakati "
"wa uundaji huhifadhiwa katika `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_DIR`ambayo kwa chaguomsingi ni"
" folda ya kontena ya `/climweb/plugins` ambayo inapaswa kupachikwa ndani ya "
"kiasi cha kisima. Inapowashwa ikiwa programu-jalizi itapatikana katika "
"saraka hii ambayo bado haijasakinishwa kwenye kontena la sasa itasakinishwa "
"upya."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:33
msgid ""
"As long as you re-use the same data volume, you should not lose any plugin "
"data even if you remove and re-create the containers. The only effect is on "
"initial container startup you might see the plugins re-installing themselves"
" if you re-created the container from scratch."
msgstr ""
"Alimradi unatumia tena kiasi sawa cha data, hupaswi kupoteza data yoyote ya "
"programu-jalizi hata ukiondoa na kuunda upya vyombo. Athari pekee ni kwenye "
"uanzishaji wa kontena wa awali unaweza kuona programu jalizi zikijisakinisha"
" tena ikiwa utaunda tena kontena kutoka mwanzo."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:37
msgid "Uninstalling a plugin installed using an environment variable"
msgstr ""
"Inasanidua programu-jalizi iliyosakinishwa kwa kutumia kitofauti cha "
"mazingira"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:39
msgid ""
"It is highly recommended that you backup your data before uninstalling a "
"plugin."
msgstr ""
"Inapendekezwa sana uhifadhi nakala ya data yako kabla ya kusanidua programu-"
"jalizi."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:41
msgid ""
"To uninstall a plugin you installed using one of `CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS`"
"  you need to make sure that you delete and recreate the container with the "
"plugin removed from the corresponding environment variable. If you fail to "
"do so and just uninstall-plugin using exec and restart, the plugin will be "
"re-installed after the restart as the environment variable will still "
"contain the old plugin"
msgstr ""
"Ili kusanidua programu-jalizi uliyosakinisha kwa kutumia moja ya "
"`CLIMWEB_PLUGIN_GIT_REPOS` unahitaji kuhakikisha kuwa unafuta na kuunda upya"
" kontena huku programu-jalizi ikiwa imeondolewa kwenye utofauti wa mazingira"
" unaolingana. Ukishindwa kufanya hivyo na tu kufuta-programu-jalizi kwa "
"kutumia exec na kuwasha upya, programu-jalizi itasakinishwa upya baada ya "
"kuanza upya kwani utofauti wa mazingira bado utakuwa na programu-jalizi ya "
"zamani."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:46
msgid "Checking which plugins are already installed"
msgstr "Kuangalia ni programu-jalizi zipi ambazo tayari zimesakinishwa"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-installation.md:48
msgid ""
"Use the `list-plugins` command or built in /climweb/plugins/list_plugins.sh "
"script to check what plugins are currently installed."
msgstr ""
"Tumia amri ya `list-plugins` au hati iliyojengwa ndani ya "
"/climweb/plugins/list_plugins.sh ili kuangalia ni programu-jalizi gani "
"zimesakinishwa kwa sasa."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:1
msgid "Plugin Overview"
msgstr "Muhtasari wa programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:3
msgid ""
"ClimWeb Plugins are custom Wagtail apps that extend the functionality of "
"ClimWeb. They can be used to add new features, modify existing ones, or "
"integrate with external services."
msgstr ""
"Programu-jalizi za ClimWeb ni programu maalum za Wagtail zinazopanua "
"utendakazi wa ClimWeb. Zinaweza kutumika kuongeza vipengele vipya, "
"kurekebisha vilivyopo, au kuunganishwa na huduma za nje."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:6
msgid "Some examples of what you can do with a Climweb plugin are:"
msgstr ""
"Baadhi ya mifano ya kile unachoweza kufanya na programu-jalizi ya Climweb "
"ni:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:8
msgid ""
"Add new country specific modules, for example for data processing, payments "
"integration etc."
msgstr ""
"Ongeza moduli mpya za nchi, kwa mfano za kuchakata data, kuunganisha malipo "
"n.k."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:9
msgid ""
"Add new page types that are not available in the core Climweb installation."
msgstr ""
"Ongeza aina mpya za kurasa ambazo hazipatikani katika usakinishaji msingi wa"
" Climweb."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:10
msgid "Integrate with 3rd party APIs or software"
msgstr "Unganisha na API au programu za watu wengine"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:11
msgid ""
"Install custom postgres extensions, system packages, python dependencies"
msgstr ""
"Sakinisha upanuzi wa postgres maalum, vifurushi vya mfumo, utegemezi wa "
"python"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:12
msgid "And much more!"
msgstr "Na mengi zaidi!"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:14
msgid "Important Notes on Plugins"
msgstr "Vidokezo Muhimu kwenye Programu-jalizi"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:16
msgid ""
"You should always make backups of your Climweb data before installing and "
"using any plugin."
msgstr ""
"Unapaswa kufanya nakala rudufu za data yako ya Climweb kila wakati kabla ya "
"kusakinisha na kutumia programu-jalizi yoyote."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:17
msgid "You should only ever install plugins from a trusted source"
msgstr ""
"Unapaswa tu kusakinisha programu-jalizi kutoka kwa chanzo kinachoaminika"

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:18
msgid ""
"Ensure that you fully understand the plugins you are installing and using, "
"as this entirely at your own risk."
msgstr ""
"Hakikisha kuwa unaelewa kikamilifu programu-jalizi unazosakinisha na "
"kutumia, kwani hii ni kwa hatari yako mwenyewe."

#: ../../_docs/technical/extending-climweb/plugin-overview.md:20
msgid ""
"In this guide we dive into how to create a Climweb plugin, discuss the "
"plugin architecture and give you sample plugins to get inspiration from."
msgstr ""
"Katika mwongozo huu tunazama katika jinsi ya kuunda programu-jalizi ya "
"Climweb, jadili usanifu wa programu-jalizi na kukupa sampuli za programu-"
"jalizi ili kupata msukumo kutoka."

